<subSubSection id="6D837C85103EFFA1DBE2FC08484528E4" pageId="27" pageNumber="128" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="25262F0E103EFFA1DBE2FC08484528E4" blockId="27.[151,1437,151,969]" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C103EFFA1DBE2FC084D0E2870" bold="true" box="[199,315,835,861]" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E299548D103EFFA1DA64FC084D852870" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[321,432,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallens">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C103EFFA1DA64FC084D852870" box="[321,432,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">A. pallens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D103EFFA1D992FC084F3A2870" box="[695,783,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nobil">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C103EFFA1D992FC084F3A2870" box="[695,783,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">A. nobil</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is from 
<collectingCountry id="5D8E6F9E103EFFA1D841FC084FE42870" box="[868,977,835,861]" name="Indonesia" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D103EFFA1DF20FC0848BD2870" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[1029,1160,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sufflavus">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C103EFFA1DF20FC0848BD2870" box="[1029,1160,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">A. sufflavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="5D8E6F9E103EFFA1DFECFC0849182870" box="[1225,1325,835,861]" name="Thailand" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">Thailand</collectingCountry>
in largely yellow body. From 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D103EFFA1DA57FC2C4DE828AC" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[370,477,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nobilis">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C103EFFA1DA57FC2C4DE828AC" box="[370,477,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">A. nobilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it can be distinguished by the shorter maxillary stylets that retracted into basal 1/3 of head, and almost entirely yellow pterothorax and abdominal tergite II. From 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D103EFFA1D8CAFCC048472888" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[1007,1138,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sufflavus">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C103EFFA1D8CAFCC048472888" box="[1007,1138,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="128">A. sufflavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it can be distinguished by the fewer setae on dorsum of distal antennal segments, and almost entirely yellow head.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
